## Project Resource Properties {#properties}

### Inputs

<pulumi-choosable type="language" values="python">
<p>
In Python, inputs that are objects can be passed either as <a href="/docs/languages-sdks/python/#inputs-and-outputs">argument classes or as dictionary literals</a>.
</p>
</pulumi-choosable>

The Project resource accepts the following [input](/docs/intro/concepts/inputs-outputs) properties:



<div>
<pulumi-choosable type="language" values="csharp">
<dl class="resources-properties"><dt class="property-required"
            title="Required">
        <span id="domainidentifier_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#domainidentifier_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Domain<wbr>Identifier</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>Identifier of domain which the project is part of. Must follow the regex of <code>^dzd[-_][a-zA-Z0-9_-]{1,36}$</code>.</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="description_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#description_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Description</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>Description of project.</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="glossaryterms_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#glossaryterms_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Glossary<wbr>Terms</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">List&lt;string&gt;</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>List of glossary terms that can be used in the project. The list cannot be empty or include over 20 values. Each value must follow the regex of <code>[a-zA-Z0-9_-]{1,36}$</code>.</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="name_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#name_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Name</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Name of the project. Must follow the regex of <code>^[\w -]+$</code>. and have a length of at most 64.</p>
<p>The following arguments are optional:</p>
</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="skipdeletioncheck_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#skipdeletioncheck_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Skip<wbr>Deletion<wbr>Check</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">bool</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>Optional flag to delete all child entities within the project.</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="timeouts_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#timeouts_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Timeouts</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type"><a href="#projecttimeouts">Project<wbr>Timeouts</a></span>
    </dt>
    <dd></dd></dl>

## Import



Using `pulumi import`, import DataZone Project using a colon-delimited string combining `domain_id` and `id`. For example:

```sh
$ pulumi import aws:datazone/project:Project example domain-1234:project-1234
```


To learn more about importing existing cloud resources, see [Importing resources](/docs/using-pulumi/adopting-pulumi/import/).
